      "role": "user",
      "content": "man i was just looking at some photos of the deep field from the james webb telescope and it just hit me... everything we do, all the stress, the heartbreak, the literally everything... it's just zero. in the grand scale of the universe, we're just a chemical accident on a speck of dust that's gonna get swallowed by heat death anyway. how can anyone even bother to get out of bed in the morning when the math just says nothing matters?",
